Bursitis of the tensor veli palatini muscle with an osteophyte on the pterygoid hamulus.
 Many patients with temporomandibular joint dysfunction and/or myofascial pain syndrome have numerous symptoms.
 In cases of multiple complaints, an attempt should be made to resolve symptoms on a step-by-step basis.
 In this case report, a patient was treated for only one of her numerous complaints, that is, a burning sensation on her palate when she touched the right tuberosity area with her tongue or finger.
